   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>The ninth year of the Emperor Caesar Nerva Trajan Augustus Germanicus Dacicus. Has worked for five days in fulfillment of his obligation of the same ninth year for work on the embankments, (2nd hand) in the new six-gate sluice from Pauni 18 to 22, (on behalf of) Karanis,  Ptollis, son of Pamenes, grandson of Tithoes, whose mother is Tanephremmis. I, Isidoros, have signed it.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography" subtype="citations">
